summary: This document is an email chain discussing the processing and tracking of FBI 302 interview reports (specifically batch 3 of 3) related to the Epstein case. It highlights internal administrative coordination regarding document labeling, duplicates, and name discrepancies between different file sets.

events.title: Transmission of 302 batch 3 of 3
events.description: An email was sent containing the third batch of FBI 302 interview reports, which includes an interview ending in the number 377.

events.title: Review and tracking of 302s
events.description: Email correspondence confirms receipt and review of the 302 batch, noting duplicates and pointing out name discrepancies between the new files and existing tracking systems.

keyFacts: The document is part of an email chain concerning FBI 302 interview reports (Form 302s) related to the Epstein investigation.
It references a specific interview within the batch that ends with the number '377'.
The correspondence notes discrepancies in how names are listed between newly received 302s and the existing tracking system, indicating ongoing administrative review and data management.
The emails are dated April 22-23, 2020, showing post-Epstein's death coordination among personnel handling the case files.
